<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,447,1228]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,699,724]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,699,724]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male: Color pattern very close to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[828,973,701,724]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ictericum">
<emphasis box="[828,973,701,724]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. ictericum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 33A–B). Cercus in lateral view: dorsobasal expansion absent. Ventrobasal expansion present but very small. Straight (Fig. 23B). Cercus in mediodorsal view: basal portion longest. 1/2 its length, medial and apical portions subequal. Medial process triangular plate, sclerotized ridge crossing process on its inner side. Apical portion pointed (Fig. 23A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,447,1228]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[199,305,843,868]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,302,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
—R. W. Garrison (pers. comm.) wrote to me about this species. He compared the 
<typeStatus box="[1244,1342,844,868]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sjostedt" authorityYear="1918" box="[151,286,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvarum">
<emphasis box="[151,286,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. silvarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with material, most collected by the Williamsons, that he considered to represent 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sjostedt" authorityYear="1918" box="[1237,1372,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvarum">
<emphasis box="[1237,1372,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. silvarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from several localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[378,450,916,940]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Garrison examined a male (Reserva Ducke, 
<quantity box="[963,1035,916,940]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="km" value="26.0">26 km</quantity>
E Manaus) that fits the incomplete 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,951,975]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sjostedt" authorityYear="1918" box="[287,419,952,976]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvarum">
<emphasis box="[287,419,952,976]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. silvarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
perfectly as to body maculation and noted representatives from other populations (Belem, Porto Velho). The appendage morphology for all agreed well with Sjöstedt's figures for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sjostedt 1918)" baseAuthorityName="Sjostedt" baseAuthorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvarum">
<emphasis box="[1189,1325,988,1012]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. silvarum</emphasis>
(Sjöstedt 1918)
</taxonomicName>
. Other material from Manaus (
<typeStatus box="[569,667,1023,1047]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[707,871,1024,1048]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanurum">
<emphasis box="[707,871,1024,1048]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. melanurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sjostedt" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[1010,1143,1024,1048]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvarum">
<emphasis box="[1010,1143,1024,1048]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. silvarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="De Marmels" firstAuthor="De Marmels" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="225 - 238" refId="ref19857" refString="De Marmels, J. (1987) On the type specimens of some neotropical Megapodagrionidae, with a description of Heteragrion pemon spec. nov. and Oxystigma caerulans spec. nov. from Venezuela (Zygoptera). Odonatologica, 16 (3), 225 - 238." type="journal article" year="1987">De Marmels (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. All comparisons with the morphology of the appendages was based on Sjöstedt's figures, as the appendages were missing when De Marmels examined the 
<typeStatus box="[686,784,1095,1119]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">holotype</typeStatus>
in 1987. Based on his examination, Garrison agrees with De Marmels that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[344,505,1132,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanurum">
